course_description: This fourth practicum focuses on leadership skills application. Emphasis is on synthesizing, appraising, and implementing evidence-based guidelines for health promotion & risk reduction when caring for complex and diverse groups of patients across the lifespan in primary and emergency care settings.
prerequisites: NRSG 732D as prerequisite and NRSG 811D as co-requisite, or equivalent transfer credit.
